The Abuja Municipal Area Council (AMAC) has disbanded its task force enforcing traffic laws in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) following reports of abuse by the officials. Chairman, AMAC, Abdullahi Candido, who announced the disbandment at a town hall meeting convened by the Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ) yesterday, apologised to residents for the conduct of the officials. He said the task force would be replaced with marshals to be trained for one month.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .